Working with SceneBuilder will definitely simplify the work :), but you need to be very careful with all the attributes it generates. Particularly in FXML file, don&#39;t include any attribute unless it is really required. 

I can observe the same in your FXML code. There are lot of unnecessary attributes which you can eliminate. In fact that will fix your issue.

Few points you can consider:
 * Understand the impact of using min/max width/height with Infinity/-Infinity
 * Remove unnecessary constraints if it is not required.
 * Understand how each layout behaves. Choosing the correct layout will really simplify the work. 
 * If you want your application to be resizable, try minimizing the usage of prefWidth/height and let the layout take care of it.

